  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I'm Miss Maya. I love that you're into Bollywood — what's a favourite scene you always rewatch?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, that’s a tough one. There are so many scenes to choose from. I like the song \"Jai Ho\" from Slumdog Millionaire. It’s so energetic and iconic. What about you — any Bollywood scenes you like?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Jai Ho\" is a brilliant choice — such a powerful song! I get why it stands out. Any other Bollywood scenes you’d pick for a playlist?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe \"Chaiyya Chaiyya\" from Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge. It's a classic. I mean, the setting is so beautiful, and the way they shot it... it feels magical. But honestly, I could watch that one scene again and again."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Chaiyya Chaiyya\" is an amazing pick — such a beautiful song and setting. Got it. What’s the next scene you’d add to your Bollywood playlist?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, maybe \"Aankhen Khuli\" from Tum Mile. The song is so emotional, and the scene has this quiet, subtle vibe. It’s different from the big, flashy ones — but that’s what makes it special for me."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"That’s a lovely choice — quiet and emotional scenes are the best for deep connection.\" What’s another kind of scene you’d enjoy in your playlist?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think I’d also pick a fun, light-hearted song like \"Laila O Laila\" from Student of the Year. It’s so much fun to watch — the energy is infectious. Sometimes you just need something that makes you smile and dance, you know? 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Laila O Laila\" is a great choice — energy like that is hard to ignore. What's a scene you'd add for pure joy?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "How about \"Ghungroo\" from Sultan? That whole scene is just so intense and emotional. Amir Khan’s performance really hits hard. It’s one of those scenes that stays with you. Yeah, I’d add that for sure. Thanks for listening, Maya! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're very welcome — \"Ghungroo\" is a scene that truly lingers. What about a comedy scene to balance it out? Any fun Bollywood ones?"
    }
  ],
